&lt;div class="stimulus-box"&gt;&lt;div class="stim-label"&gt;Stimulus&lt;/div&gt;A thematic map of Sub-Saharan Africa uses color gradients to show countries by total population, with darker shades indicating larger populations. Nigeria appears the darkest shade, while several island nations appear nearly white.&lt;/div&gt;
