&lt;span id="acnt"&gt;0 answered&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="focus-banner"&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Exam 2 design notes:&lt;/strong&gt; Unit weights now match College Board's official distribution (Units 1 &amp; 2 = ~11% each; Units 3–7 = ~11–14% each with Urban/Political heavier). MCQ distractors are rebalanced — no answer choice is systematically longer than others. FRQ 2-C directly retests Von Thünen ring order (your Exam 1 miss). FRQ 3-F retests the "explain X &lt;em&gt;and&lt;/em&gt; ONE limitation" two-part structure (your Exam 1 miss). Impact big idea parts are marked &lt;span style="color:var(--impact-color);font-weight:700;"&gt;⬡ IMPACT&lt;/span&gt;.
